SIMPLE: foresight
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foresight
<hw>Fore"sight`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act or the power of foreseeing; prescience; foreknowledge.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Action in reference to the future; provident care;
prudence; wise forethought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This seems an unseasonable <qex>foresight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A random expense, without plan or <qex>foresight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Surv.)</fld> <def>Any sight or reading of the
leveling staff, except the backsight; any sight or bearing taken by a
compass or theodolite in a forward direction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Gun.)</fld> <def>Muzzle sight. See <cref>Fore
sight</cref>, under <er>Fore</er>, <pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foresighted</ent>⟦br⟧
